Quick Start
------------------------

(1) Execute the DDL (sql/hsql.sql or sql/sybase.sql) on your database server.
(2) Execute the sample data SQL script (sql/subject.sql, sql/subsystem.sql, sql/tree.sql).
(3) Create a "signet" web application context in your servlet container.
(4) Point the web application context to the webapp/signet directory in this distribution.
(5) Copy your JDBC driver to the webapp/signet/WEB-INF/lib directory
(6) Set your database connection parameter (i.e. URL, username, password) in webapp/signet/WEB-INF/classes/hibernate.cfg.xml.
(7) Set your preferred hibernate logging level in webapp/signet/WEB-INF/classes/log4.properties.
(8) Change the feedback href in webapp/signet/footer.jsp to point to your preferred email address.


